    "3231384f-d01f-4917-ab9f-1c9b9caf22ec": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "This trap is built into the corridor of an old Shinto shrine. Concealed beneath wooden floor panels carved with sakura motifs, a pressure plate triggers a spring-loaded array of razor-sharp metal petals stored in the corridor’s ceiling. The petals fire outward in a 15-foot cone, then rain down over a 5-foot square on the floor. The mechanism can be disarmed by carefully freeing the panel and jamming the spring (requires thieves’ tools and a successful DC 14 Intelligence (Investigation) check). It resets only by manually recoiling the spring and replacing the floor panel (30 minutes).",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "886f571f-1566-4838-9aa3-d077f2c51784",
      "styles": {
        "paddingBottom": "8px"
      },
      "id": "3231384f-d01f-4917-ab9f-1c9b9caf22ec"
    },
    "49337ba2-45a2-4f2e-b6a2-d86b54fda313": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Description",
              "textFormat": "underline-h2"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "886f571f-1566-4838-9aa3-d077f2c51784",
      "id": "49337ba2-45a2-4f2e-b6a2-d86b54fda313"
    },
    "b2d91363-6979-46d5-8023-396eddb08125": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "You step into a dimly lit corridor lined with weathered torii gates. The floorboards are polished smooth, each panel bearing a faint sakura blossom carving. A soft wind chime echoes in the distance, though no breeze stirs.",
              "textFormat": "description"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "886f571f-1566-4838-9aa3-d077f2c51784",
      "styles": {
        "paddingBottom": "8px"
      },
      "id": "b2d91363-6979-46d5-8023-396eddb08125"
    },
    "5f0954b0-2cfd-41dc-bd30-da13384285fe": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Skill Checks",
              "textFormat": "underline-h2"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "886f571f-1566-4838-9aa3-d077f2c51784",
      "id": "5f0954b0-2cfd-41dc-bd30-da13384285fe"
    },
    "97b042c4-8090-44bc-9fdf-30cb61a42d7f": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "DC 13 Wisdom (Perception):: ",
              "textFormat": "paragraph",
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "text": "You notice faint scratch marks around one particular panel and slight discoloration along the seam, hinting at a concealed mechanism.",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "DC 14 Intelligence (Investigation):: ",
              "textFormat": "paragraph",
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "text": "Careful inspection reveals a thin spring coil tucked beneath the carved panel, which you identify as part of a trap’s firing mechanism.",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "DC 14 Dexterity (Thieves’ Tools):: ",
              "textFormat": "paragraph",
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "text": "You delicately pry up the floor panel and jam the coil, preventing the petals from launching.",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "886f571f-1566-4838-9aa3-d077f2c51784",
      "styles": {
        "paddingBottom": "8px"
      },
      "id": "97b042c4-8090-44bc-9fdf-30cb61a42d7f"
    },
    "63cff638-e236-470c-9bf5-ce094f3ea7a1": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "Consequence",
              "textFormat": "underline-h2"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "886f571f-1566-4838-9aa3-d077f2c51784",
      "id": "63cff638-e236-470c-9bf5-ce094f3ea7a1"
    },
    "36bf01ab-6674-41b7-b0df-17dec667c922": {
      "type": "simple",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "children": [
            {
              "text": "When a creature steps on the hidden panel without first disabling the mechanism, razor petals fire in a 15-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking 6d6 slashing damage on a failed save, or half as much on a success. Immediately afterward, the petals rain down and cover the 5-foot square beneath the trap. That square becomes difficult terrain, and any creature that starts its turn there takes 2d6 slashing damage from the embedded blades.",
              "textFormat": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "parentId": "886f571f-1566-4838-9aa3-d077f2c51784",
      "styles": {
        "paddingBottom": "8px"
      },
      "id": "36bf01ab-6674-41b7-b0df-17dec667c922"
    }
